title.narrative: DFID Emergency Medical Team and associated procurement supplies

description.narrative: This activity (DFID Emergency Medical Team and associated procurement supplies) is a component of Humanitarian Emergency Response Operations and Stabilisation Programme (HEROS) reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of goods' and a budget of £6,042,959. This component benefits Developing countries, unspecified, and works in the following sector(s): Material relief assistance and services . , with the following implementing partners: DAI Europe, Palladium International Ltd (UK), UK-Med. The start date is 01-11-2017 and the end date is 28-10-2022.
